    "leafs": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Maple Leafs",
      "league": "NHL",
      "record": "32-36-14",
      "detail": "8th in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The curtain crashed down on another Toronto Maple Leafs season - a grim 32-36-14 slog that left them <strong>8th in the Atlantic, 31 games back with just 78 points and a seven-game losing streak to cap the misery</strong>. No playoffs, no miracles, just the cold reality of missing the dance for the second straight year, buried at 15th in the seedings. The core - Matthews, Marner, Tavares - flickered but never ignited, outscored and outmuscled by a division that feasted on their inconsistency. Goaltending crumbled under pressure; the blue line leaked like a sieve. Now the reckoning: Shanahan's seat scorches hotter than Scotiabank Arena ice, with whispers of a coaching purge swirling. Free agency looms with cap hell ahead - who stays, who goes? Draft lottery balls tumble soon, offering a sliver of hope for talent infusion. <strong>Watch the front office this week: one bold trade or firing could redefine the rebuild - or doom another lost summer</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
